This paper deals with the task of identifying misogyny in online content using machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves feature engineering and model selection, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves text classification, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
